{"lemma":"أَزْرِ","slug":"أَزْرِ","root":"#.ز.ر","root_slug":"_-ز-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ز-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَزْر","root":"أزر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n658","n659","n660"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prop up, to assist, to support","examples":[{"text":"وَمَثَلُهُمْ فِي ٱلْإِنْجِيلِ كَزَرْعٍ أَخْرَجَ شَطْأَهُ فَآزَرَهُ فَٱسْتَغْلَظَ فَٱسْتَوَىٰ عَلَىٰ سُوقِهِ"}]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"the caretaker of Abraham, believed by Sunnis to be his father (i.e. Terah) and by Shi'ites to be his paternal uncle.","examples":[{"text":"وَإِذْ قَالَ إِبْرَاهِيمُ لِأَبِيهِ آزَرَ أَتَتَّخِذُ أَصْنَامًا آلِهَةً إِنِّي أَرَاكَ وَقَوْمَكَ فِي ضَلَالٍ مُّبِينٍ","english":"Remember when Abraham said to his father Āzar: Takest thou idols for gods? Aye! I see thee and thy folk in error manifest."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of إِزَار (ʔizār, “drawers”). Compare equipped weightlifting.\n\nFrom Hebrew אֱלִיעֶזֶר (ʾelī-ʿezer, “Eliezer”), same source as of عَازِر (ʕāzir, “Ezra”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n658","headword_ar":"اَزْرٌ","root":"Azr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strength."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, A, K.) ―         -b2-  And (or as some say, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus bearing two contr. significations. (IAar, K.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Au$odudo bihi A^azoriY","text_ar":"اُشْدُدْ بِهِ اَزْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xx. 32], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strengthen Thou by him my back:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confirm Thou by him my strength:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strengthen Thou by him my weakness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aid, assistance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"help."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-  Also, (S,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uzorN","text_ar":"اُزْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two flanks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAr","text_ar":"اـِزَار"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is tied in a knot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["IAar","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n659","headword_ar":"اُزْرٌ","root":"Azr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azorN","text_ar":"اَزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n660","headword_ar":"اـِزْرٌ","root":"Azr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaArN","text_ar":"اـِزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}